node.text: Paul Veneto regularly worked the route taken by United Airlines Flight 175, but he had the day off when the plane crashed into the World Trade Center on Sept. 11, 2001. In honor of his fallen colleagues, the retired flight attendant has spent the past three weeks walking from Boston Logan Airport to Ground Zero in New York City, pushing an airline beverage cart the whole way. ❤️ "I can now finally give tribute to my fallen crew members," he said. Tap the bio link for the full inspiring story. |#Regram, @pauliespush
